{"id":"2004.11346","submitter":"Haizhao Yang","authors":"James Bremer and Ze Chen and Haizhao Yang","title":"Rapid Application of the Spherical Harmonic Transform via Interpolative\n  Decomposition Butterfly Factorization","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NA cs.NA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We describe an algorithm for the application of the forward and inverse\nspherical harmonic transforms. It is based on a new method for rapidly\ncomputing the forward and inverse associated Legendre transforms by\nhierarchically applying the interpolative decomposition butterfly factorization\n(IDBF). Experimental evidence suggests that the total running time of our\nmethod -- including all necessary precomputations -- is $\\mathcal{O}(N^2\n\\log^3(N))$, where $N$ is the order of the transform. This is nearly\nasymptotically optimal. Moreover, unlike existing algorithms which are\nasymptotically optimal or nearly so, the constant in the running time of our\nalgorithm is small enough to make it competitive with state-of-the-art\n$\\mathcal{O}\\left(N^3\\right)$ methods at relatively small values of $N$.\nNumerical results are provided to demonstrate the effectiveness and numerical\nstability of the new framework.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Apr 2020 17:44:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 3 Oct 2020 14:21:37 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 10 Feb 2021 01:16:52 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 28 Aug 2021 17:44:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-31"}
