near field and far field,\nthe correlation angle retains the same order of magnitude (0.15$\\pi$ -\n0.7$\\pi$) for all considered Xs. While the excitation of dipolar localized\nsurface phonons (LSPhs) does not affect the correlation length and angle, the\nmultipolar LSPhs reduce the spatial coherence in both directions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Apr 2020 04:26:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 27 Apr 2020 00:39:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-28"}
